    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith the improvements to exrc, using `.nvim.lua` as project-specific configuration seems the way to go. However, `exrc` will only look in the current directory, which for project configurations will only work if Neovim is always launched in the root directory of a project.\n\nI think Neovim should check for `.nvim.lua` files recursively upwards from the current directory, stopping at the first `.nvim.lua` file encountered.\n\n---\n\nSo far, I haven't found a plugin that takes care of this using Neovim's exrc + trust mechanism.\n\n- <https://github.com/ahmedkhalf/project.nvim> changes the working directory _after_ exrc logic is run.\n- <https://github.com/jedrzejboczar/exrc.nvim> provides a `source_up` mechanism, but that needs to be invoked manually from the `.nvim.lua` file. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWith exrc enabled, load `.nvim.lua` from parent directories.",
